data.value: Bill Bourbon's Butler. The Butler at Bourbon Mansion was a fine and loyal employee according to all of the residents and tenants. He held his postion with dignity, and seemed to have nothing against Bill Bourbon. He has been super involved in the investigation, and shows interest in gettin' to the bottom of things. According to him, the pistol used to shoot Mr. Bourbon was kept under lock and key in a secret location, and could only be acessed by someone who already knew where it was. The pistol apparently went missing a day before the murder. He tried to look for it, but nobody would tell him anything relating to it's where abouts.
